# ==============================================================================
# .gitignore — Stats-Dept
# Google Apps Script (clasp) + Node tooling + macOS
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHY: Keep secrets, machine-specific junk, and installable dependencies OUT of
# version control. Anything a collaborator can regenerate or that is sensitive
# should not be committed.
# ==============================================================================

# --- Secrets / credentials (NEVER commit) -------------------------------------
# clasp's global OAuth credentials live in your HOME dir, but if a local copy is
# ever created here, it must never be committed.
.clasprc.json
# Environment files that may hold API keys or config secrets.
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem

# --- Node tooling (clasp is installed via npm) --------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
package-lock.json.bak

# --- macOS system files -------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?

# --- Editor / IDE -------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/

# --- Logs / temp --------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp

# ==============================================================================
# NOTE: We intentionally DO commit the following (do not ignore them):
#   - .clasp.json      (per-project Script ID "wiring" — not a secret; needed
#                        so collaborators can pull/push the same cloud project)
#   - appsscript.json  (Apps Script manifest — part of the source)
#   - _original-exports/ (baseline snapshot of the pre-Git .gs/.html exports)
# ==============================================================================
